<br>
It's been two days since Zarius dissapeared. No ransom demands, no clues at all. Blood Circle's Guild Leader has simply vanished from the face of Norrath. <br>
And yet, the tension still builds.  Dark forces of Hate and Anger gather around the building.  It is like the storm, building in the distance... something will break soon and the torrent shall be released.<br>
<br>
Perhaps Thorvan, meditating in Thurgadin will find the answers before it is too late.<br>
<br>
As she checks the straps of her breastplate, she reflects upon her mission... to go alone into the forest and stand a vigil.  To seek communion and guidance from the goddess. She takes a deep breath and calms her racing thoughts. <br>
 <br>
Events of the past few weeks have thrown her life into chaos. She can feel the answer to Zarious' disappearance just out of her reach, but it will not come to her. Heart-torn between duty and love, she has lost her way.  Today she will go into the forest and sing prayers, hopefully the Mother of All will assist her in regaining her center and balance.  Then, Centuri hopes, the answers will come. <br>
<br>
She dons her helm and is concious of those that watch...<br>
Her thoughts wander from her sister's quiet support and encouragement to another, who had many harsh words for her in a darkened hallway the previous evening... she can feel his dark gaze prickling the hairs on the back of her neck, right now.<br>
<br>
<br>
